  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nRemote wallets created before 1.0.4 do not have \r\n```\r\n\"require_tls\": true,\r\n```\r\nCausing an error when trying to start a validator that used tls with remote signer previously.\r\nAdding require_tls fixes the issue.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nThere was no issues in versions before 1.0.4\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nStart a validator on version 1.0.3 or lower and use a keymanageropts.json with the form of \r\n \r\n```\r\n{\r\n\t\"remote_cert\": {\r\n\t\t\"crt_path\":\r\n\t\t\"key_path\": \r\n\t\t\"ca_crt_path\":\r\n\t},\r\n\t\"remote_address\": \r\n}\r\n```\r\nAnd connect to a remote-signer with tls. The above format was the format keymanageropts.json was created in older versions. In 1.0.4 it has the \"require_tls\": true, field.\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nlevel=fatal msg=\"Could not wait for validator activation: could not fetch validating keys: could not list accounts from remote server: rpc error: code = Unavailable desc = connection closed\" prefix=validator\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nubuntu\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\n1.0.4\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
